+{"id":"frankenpandas-cz3gf","title":"fd90.180: README assign_fn example calls non-existent compute_ratio_column","description":"fd90.74-179 self-review. The README's Apply and Transform example at lines 663-668 shows:

  let df2 = df.assign_fn(vec![
      ("ratio", Box::new(|df| {
          // Compute new column from existing DataFrame
          Ok(compute_ratio_column(df))
      })),
  ])?;

compute_ratio_column is a fictional placeholder — it doesn't exist anywhere. A user copy-pasting hits:
  error[E0425]: cannot find function `compute_ratio_column` in this scope

Same pattern as fd90.162's compute_weight fix. Other examples in the README compile cleanly when imported via prelude::*.

Fix: replace with an inline expression that actually computes a Column. E.g. extract two existing columns and compute their ratio inline. Pure README change.","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-26T17:49:43.918051Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-26T17:51:06.219796847Z","closed_at":"2026-04-26T17:51:06.217117275Z","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
